.TH _PRINTF 3 "April 2026" "Version 1.0" "Custom Library Functions"

.SH NAME
_printf \- formatted output conversion

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.PP
.B int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
The _printf() function produces output according to a format string.
Output is written to the standard output stream (stdout).

The format string may contain plain text and format specifiers
introduced by the percent character (%).

Supported format specifiers:
.TP
.B %c
Print a character.
.TP
.B %s
Print a string.
.TP
.B %d
Print a signed decimal integer.
.TP
.B %i
Print a signed decimal integer.

.SH RETURN VALUE
Upon successful return, _printf() returns the number of characters printed
(excluding the terminating null byte).

If an error occurs, the function returns -1.

.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
#include "main.h"

int main(void)
{
    _printf("Hello %s\\n", "World");
    return (0);
}
.fi

